      "LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:470",
      "LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:483",
      "LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:493"
    ],
    "claim": "`repayBorrowInternal` snapshots `borrowedAmount` before external token transfer, then executes full-repay cleanup (`removeBorrowBalance`) based on that stale snapshot; a callback-capable token can reenter and create fresh debt before cleanup runs.",
    "impact": "An attacker can end the transaction with newly borrowed funds while internal debt tracking is deleted, leaving untracked/socialized bad debt and insolvency risk.",
    "paths": [
      "Attacker uses a callback-capable borrowed token and calls `repayBorrow(type(uint256).max, lToken)`.",
      "During `safeTransferFrom`, callback reenters `borrow(...)` and opens new debt before outer state update.",
      "Outer call sees `repayAmountFinal == borrowedAmount` from the stale pre-callback snapshot and deletes borrow state."
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "F-039",
    "severity": "Medium",
    "confidence": "medium",
    "title": "Same-chain liquidation credits seized collateral without adding liquidator supplied-asset membership",
    "locations": [
      "LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:307",
      "LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:310"
    ],
    "claim": "`liquidateSeizeUpdate` increases `totalInvestment` for the liquidator but never calls `addUserSuppliedAsset` for that collateral market.",
    "impact": "Seized collateral can be excluded from liquidity/collateral calculations, making liquidators appear undercollateralized and enabling avoidable follow-on liquidations against assets they just seized.",
    "paths": [
      "Liquidator with existing debt liquidates a borrower and receives a new collateral market.",
      "That market is not inserted into `userSuppliedAssets`, so `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral` ignores it.",
